body:
### Steps to reproduce

I happen to be creating a new Rails test app a few hours ago  when 7.1.3.2 was released. 

A stimulus controller I've used for years all of a sudden produced an error

```ruby
The resource http://localhost:3000/assets/controllers/flashIt.controller-
d7fc6bd02d113b8faec8c95d343483bb35099e6a6f269f9a13f0de5796578850.js 
was preloaded using link preload but not used within a few seconds from the window's load event.
 Please make sure it wasn't preloaded for nothing.
```

The markup that loads the controller

```slim
div.col-span-6
      - flash.each do |name, msg|
        - if msg.is_a?(String)
          .flash-box.w3-animate-right.p-2[
            data-controller="flashIt" 
            data-flashIt-target="flashBox" 
            class="#{name.to_s == 'notice' ? 'text-green-500 bg-green-100 px-4' : 'p-2 text-red-500 bg-red-100 px-4'}"
          ]
            = content_tag :span, content_tag(:strong,msg)
```

The controller

```javascript
import { Controller } from "@hotwired/stimulus"

export default class extends Controller {
  static targets = [ "flashBox" ]

  connect() {
    this.closeFlashIt()
  }

  closeFlashIt(){
    var box = this.flashBoxTarget
    setTimeout(function () {
      var op = 1;  // initial opacity
        var timer = setInterval(function () {
            if (op <= 0.1){
                clearInterval(timer);
                box.style.display = 'none';
            }
            box.style.opacity = op;
            box.style.filter = 'alpha(opacity=' + op * 100 + ")";
            op -= op * 0.1;
        }, 500);
    }, 10000);
  }
}
```
The flash message will show up if there is a flash message, but it won't fade out.

The message first shows up in the js console shortly after the page is loaded (it's on every page since it's in the menubar. I opened the console when the message did not fade out.

